    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "WACO \u2013\nThe Sam Houston Bearkats saw their 4-game win streak come to an end on Tuesday night, dropping an 13-5 decision to Baylor at Baylor Ballpark.\nHunter Alvord\nand\nCade Corcoran\nhad two hits and an RBI apiece for the Kats (8-8), but the first seven Bearkat hits in the game were singles before back-to-back 2-out doubles by\nEaston Dean\nand\nKirby Orth\nto plate the game's final run; meanwhile, the Bears (10-6) had six of their 15 hits go for extra bases, including three homers.\nJakob Holzer\ngot his second midweek start of the year for Sam Houston and had four strikeouts but was tagged with the loss after allowing five runs on eight hits in 2.2 frames of work.\nCooper Harris\n,\nNoah Kendrick\n,\nJonathan Anders\nand\nConnor Mondey\ncombined for five\u00a0more punchouts, giving the SHSU staff nine strikeouts for the game.\nBaylor starter Cayden Baker got his first win of the year as the first of six Bear arms on a staff day, allowing one run in 2.0 innings before giving way to the bullpen.\nThe Kats manufactured a run in the opening inning on an RBI grounder by\nWes Baker\nbut Baylor immediately answered, tying it with two outs in the bottom of the first on a solo homer from Brady Janusek.\nThe Bears added on in each of next three innings, taking the lead on an RBI single by Travis Sanders in the second and pushing the lead to 5-1 in the third on a no-doubt solo homer by Tyce Armstrong, an RBI single by Brytton Clements and a Bearkat passed ball with a runner on third base.\nThe Kats put together a threat in the fourth with 1-out singles by Alvord and Corcoran but missed getting back on the scoreboard when Bear reliever Luke McLeod got\nNathan Fink\nto fly out to the wall in straightaway center field and then ended the threat with a strikeout of\nBlake Brown\n.\nHarris put up a zero in the fourth on the mound, but Baylor got its third solo home run of the game in the fifth when Hunter Snow greeted Kendrick with a blast to right field to push the lead to 6-1.\nSam Houston pushed three runs across to draw to within two at 6-4. Alvord and Corcoran each delivered RBI singles and the Kats had runners on the corners with nobody out, but Baylor reliever Cade McFaddin was able to kill the rally with a double-play grounder off the bat of Fink that scored a run but also cleared the bases.\nUnfortunately, the Bearkats were unable to put up a shutdown inning in the bottom half of the frame as the Bears answered right back with a matching 3-spot. Hits from JJ Kennett and Pearson Riebock got BU going, but the Kats were their own worst enemy in the inning, committing a pair of errors on a grounder off the bat of Janusek that allowed a pair of runs to come in and set up the third.\nBaylor biggest scoring inning of the night in the bottom of the eighth, capping the scoring with four runs on RBI hits from Janusek, Armstrong and Clements and the third Bearkat error of the night.\nUP NEXT\nSam Houston will return to Don Sanders Stadium this weekend, opening Conference USA play with three games against Jax State. The series is set to kick off Friday night with first pitch set for 6:35 p.m."
  },
